comments: Excellent professor. Knows his stuff, and puts up with a lot out of his disruptive students graciously. Could do a little better with class discipline, but in a masters level class you would expect them to do this on their own.

I have had the pleasure of having Jaeger 3 times for 3 different classes. Anatomy and ONE are fine in fact they are pretty darn good, but I would NOT take him again for Biology - he has no enthusiasm for the subject and reads out loud from the text book during 3/4 of the class (yawn).
Didn\'t learn much but it was easy.

Dr. J is a great professor who is extremely engaging. i have him for a 9am class and without fail, people are always attentive in his class. i rarely lose focus despite how early it is. he does a great job teaching about the bones and muscles and frequently finds ways to throw in funny-yet still relevant stories. i recommend him highly for anatomy.
Friendly. Good person, horrible teacher though. All we did was just get read to in class. He did an awful and misleading job in the finals review class.

Clearly he does not prepare for class. He spends the majority of class simply reading out loud from the textbook. Lame. This is a Masters Degree program, and this guy is reading out loud from the text book? I mean come on! If you ask questions he usually says "I don\'t know" and keeps reading. If you have a choice, choose a different prof.
I\'ve heard his anatomy class is a lot different, but for Bio, he just reads from the textbook for the whole class.
Awesome professor...actually helps you learn. Keeps the class interesting.

He cares about his students learning, is passionate about what he teaches (is a chiropractor), does a great job of articulating and giving helpful associations to learn the bones and muscles of the body
